title: For Trade:  Nickle plated Winchester mod. 63
postcontent: I have a Winchester model 63 that I believe was factory nickle plated. It was made in 1938. As the depression was still in full swing, Winchester would do about anything for a sale. You could order a gun any way you wanted it. It was common back then for a hardware or sporting goods store to raffle off a .22 rifle, and what better way to draw attention than a nickle plated one in the front window. There's no way to tell how many of these were ordered but I would have to guess at least 50. It's still a rare rifle, though. Anyway, I would like to trade it for something else. I never have shot it. Just don't care for the clack, clack of a model 63 as it cycles. The rifle has some minor rust on the rear sight and you can tell it has been shot some. Make me an offer of something you would be willing to trade for it. I am valuing it conservatively at $800. It's probably worth a good deal more.....
